<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FF3F72D5DDDDFDEC" bold="true" box="[192,707,511,535]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FF3F72D5DEF9FDEC" authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[192,487,511,535]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oenides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FF3F72D5DE33FDEC" bold="true" box="[192,301,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Oenides</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
is a valid genus
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E5BFFD7FF17711BDABEFD50" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E5BFFD7FF17711BDABEFD50" blockId="41.[192,1440,560,683]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FF17711BDEA4FDB3" box="[232,442,560,584]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpina">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FF17711BDEA4FDB3" box="[232,442,560,584]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Hesperia vulpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C. and R. Felder, 1867 is not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FBEF711ADBACFDB3" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[1040,1202,560,584]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FBEF711ADBACFDB3" box="[1040,1202,560,584]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Alera furcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5BFFD7FB0F711BDA3BFDB2" box="[1264,1317,561,585]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FF3F717BDE1CFD92" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[192,258,593,617]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FF3F717BDE1CFD92" box="[192,258,593,617]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Alera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FE9A717BDEF6FD92" box="[357,488,593,617]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpina">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FE9A717BDEF6FD92" box="[357,488,593,617]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">H. vulpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously placed, and since it is the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E5BFFD7FC107178DB3AFD91" box="[1007,1060,594,618]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
species of the available genusgroup name 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FEAA715BDD7DFD71" authority="Mabille, 1904" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1904" box="[341,611,625,650]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oenides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FEAA715BDEA8FD72" box="[341,438,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Oenides</emphasis>
Mabille, 1904
</taxonomicName>
, that was considered a subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FB7A715BDBD9FD72" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[1157,1223,625,649]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Alera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FB7A715BDBD9FD72" box="[1157,1223,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Alera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we resurrect this genus from synonymy and use it as a monotypic valid genus with the species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E5BFFD7FB9871B8DA33FD51" box="[1127,1325,658,682]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Oenides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpina">
<emphasis id="B95344267E5BFFD7FB9871B8DA33FD51" box="[1127,1325,658,682]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Oenides vulpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E5BFFD7FAC371B9DA8CFD50" box="[1340,1426,659,683]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="39.[192,275,1562,1584]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,215,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[192,1440,213,1528]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 13. Genomic trees of Hesperiina, Pericharini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677261/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
